Date: Tue 13 Nov 2007
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2007; 20(46) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Rift Valley fever, Sudan
------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 11 Nov 2007 from Dr Bashir Taha
Mohamed Taha, undersecretary federal Ministry of Animal Resources and
chief veterinary officer, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Animal
Resources, Khartoum, Sudan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 8 Oct 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 29 Oct 2007
Report date: 11 Nov 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 11 Nov 2007
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: June 1973
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Rift Valley fever [RVF] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
Report pertains to: entire country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Zilait (White Nile)
Species: sheep
Susceptible: 400
Cases:
Deaths:
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Species: cattle
Susceptible: 110
Cases:
Deaths:
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Outbreak statistics
Species: sheep
Apparent morbidity rate: 0 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: -
Proportion susceptible removed*: 0 percent

Species: cattle
Apparent morbidity rate: 0 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: -
Proportion susceptible removed*: 0 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of infection: vectors

Epidemiological comments: vaccine importation is in process.
Samples will be sent for confirmation to the OIE Reference
Laboratory, Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute (South Africa).

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Research Laboratory,
Soba (National laboratory)
Species: sheep
Test: enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA)
Test date: 29 Oct 2007
Result: positive

